<div class="block">
      
  <div class="content">
    <div class="full-title with-title-branding">
      <div class="title-branding"><a href="/taxonomy/term/868"><img src="https://www2.bfi.org.uk/sites/bfi.org.uk/files/styles/16x9_small/public/sight-and-sound-logo-280x69.png?itok=AEegRSbk" alt="" /></a></div>
  
  <h1>
          The essay film    
    
      </h1>

  
  
        <div class="copy">
              <div class="intro"><p>In recent years the essay film has attained widespread recognition as a particular category of film practice, with its own history and canonical figures and texts. In tandem with a major season throughout August at London&#8217;s BFI Southbank, Sight <span class="amp">&amp;</span> Sound explores the characteristics that have come to define this most elastic of forms and looks in detail at a dozen influential milestone essay films.</p>
</div>
            
      
              <p class="author-data">
          <span class="author"> Andrew  Tracy  , <a href="/people/catherine-mcgahan"> Katy  McGahan  </a>, <a href="/people/olaf-m-ller"> Olaf  Möller  </a>,  Sergio  Wolf  ,  Nina  Power  </span><br /><span class="date">Updated: <time datetime="2019-05-07">7 May 2019</time></span>        </p>
      
      
          </div>
  </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="block">
      
  <div class="content">
    
  <ul class="share">
          <li class="facebook_share"><div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://www2.bfi.org.uk/news-opinion/sight-sound-magazine/features/deep-focus/essay-film" data-layout="button_count"></div>
</li>
